name: treatment of waste polystyrene, unsanitary landfill, very wet infiltration class (1000mm) | waste polystyrene | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/18069/documentation

This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of 'waste polystyrene' in an unsanitary landfill. Recommended use of this dataset: for PS, which goes to disposal as part of managed communal waste mixture. For Expanded PS (EPS) use other dataset. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% PS.   ;Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 38.88 MJ/kg; net heating value 38.67 MJ/kg; H2O 2000; O 38852; H 78046; C 868490; S 678.75; N 1942.6; P na; B na; Cl 1132.1; Br 882.12; F 14.25; I na; Ag na; As 1.8418; Ba 180.79; Cd 23.336; Co 30.622; Cr 39.613; Cu 107.56; Hg 0.82311; Mn 77.469; Mo na; Ni 19.968; Pb 14.935; Sb 41.65; Se 2.0357; Sn 25.403; V 279.32; Zn 834.61; Be 0.48468; Sc na; Sr 85.789; Ti 969.36; Tl 0.38774; W na; Si na; Fe 3611.5; Ca na; Al 193.87; K na; Mg na; Na 1420.6.   ;Share of carbon in initial waste that is biogenic 0%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 1%. 0.0003235 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period.

The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included.

The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to air via landfill gas, and to water via leachate.
category: E:Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities/38:Waste collection, treatment and disposal activities; materials recovery/382:Waste treatment and disposal/3821:Treatment and disposal of non-hazardous waste

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: This dataset represents a landfill of 'infiltration class 5 very wet'. Landfill site with mean annual temperature (MAT) of 8 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 1900 mm/year, and net infiltration of 1000 mm/year. Temperature at site can result in permafrost conditions, which slows down water flow by a factor of (alpha t) 0.999. Total climate adjustments with alpha pt of 0.999. The leachate percolating through the landfill has an average residence time of 3.75 years.;Reference for climatic parameters: Doka, G., 2018, Inventory parameters for regionalised waste disposal mixes
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: This is an inventory for an unsanitary, sub-controlled landfill for municipal solid waste. Ultimate average landfill height is 15 meters. Operation phase duration is 25 years. The total raw landfill gas mass produced in the landfill from this waste is 0.00887 kg. The total CH4 mass in the raw landfill gas is 0.006213 kg. Percentage of landfill gas directly emitted is 100w%. Leachate of the landfill is not treated, but emitted untreated. Based on average waste composition and climate data the end of carbonate phase is estimated to be reached 1733 years after waste deposition.
